    {
      "id": 99, "type": "text", "title": "",
      "gridPos": {"h": 4, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 54},
      "options": {"mode": "markdown", "content": "**References & data sources**\n\n- **Local plugin inventory** — Grafana `/api/plugins?embedded=0` (provides `info.version`, `hasUpdate`, `signature`, `angularDetected`, `dependencies.grafanaDependency`)\n- **Marketplace** — `https://grafana.com/api/plugins` (provides `version` (latest), `orgName` (publisher), `downloads`, `popularity`)\n- **Runtime metrics** — Prometheus `grafana_plugin_request_total`, `grafana_datasource_request_duration_seconds_bucket`\n\n**Why some cells say _Bundled with Grafana_:** Built-in panels (alertlist, dashlist, …) ship as part of Grafana core and don't expose a separate version, and built-in datasources are not in the public marketplace. The displayed string reflects that fact rather than leaving cells blank.\n\n**Why _Grafana Dependency_ may be `—`:** It's read from the **local** plugin manifest (`dependencies.grafanaDependency`). If a plugin author didn't declare it, the field is empty — the marketplace LIST endpoint also doesn't expose it, only the per-plugin endpoint does."}
    }
  ]
}
